HEADWORD: Self-conceited
<hw>Self`-con*ceit"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having an overweening
opinion of one's own powers, attainments; vain; conceited.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Self`-con*ceit"ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
